This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) algorithm. The paper also incorporates machine learning and neural network uncertainty, which suggests it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper's feature selection strategy involves Bayesian neural networks, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of the KITTI odometry dataset suggests it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
